etymologies: mid 17th century. From post-classical Latin impervestigabilis unsearchable, inscrutable from classical Latin im- + pervestigāre + -bilis, after Hellenistic Greek ἀνεξιχνίαστος (Septuagint: Job 5:9; New Testament: Romans 11:33, Ephesians 3:8)

definitions: That cannot be sought into, examined, or understood; uninvestigable.
